---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '@components/CodeBlock.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Contributing - React to PDF"
  description="Learn how to contribute to React to PDF"
>
  <div class="contributing-container">
    <h1>Contributing to React to PDF</h1>

    <p class="intro">
      Thank you for your interest in contributing to React to PDF! We welcome contributions
      from the community.
    </p>

    <section>
      <h2>Getting Started</h2>

      <h3>1. Fork and Clone</h3>
      <CodeBlock
        code={`# Fork the repository on GitHub, then clone your fork
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/react-to-pdf.git
cd react-to-pdf`}
        language="bash"
      />

      <h3>2. Install Dependencies</h3>
      <CodeBlock
        code={`npm install`}
        language="bash"
      />

      <h3>3. Run Tests</h3>
      <CodeBlock
        code={`npm test`}
        language="bash"
      />

      <h3>4. Build the Project</h3>
      <CodeBlock
        code={`npm run build`}
        language="bash"
      />
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Development Workflow</h2>

      <ol>
        <li><strong>Create a branch</strong> for your feature or fix:
          <CodeBlock
            code={`git checkout -b feature/my-new-feature`}
            language="bash"
          />
        </li>

        <li><strong>Make your changes</strong> and write tests if applicable</li>

        <li><strong>Run tests</strong> to ensure everything works:
          <CodeBlock
            code={`npm test`}
            language="bash"
          />
        </li>

        <li><strong>Commit your changes</strong> with a descriptive message:
          <CodeBlock
            code={`git commit -m "Add new feature: description of feature"`}
            language="bash"
          />
        </li>

        <li><strong>Push to your fork</strong>:
          <CodeBlock
            code={`git push origin feature/my-new-feature`}
            language="bash"
          />
        </li>

        <li><strong>Open a Pull Request</strong> on GitHub</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Code Guidelines</h2>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>TypeScript</strong> - All code should be written in TypeScript</li>
        <li><strong>Tests</strong> - Add tests for new features using Vitest</li>
        <li><strong>Code Style</strong> - Follow existing code style (we use ESLint)</li>
        <li><strong>Documentation</strong> - Update docs for new features</li>
        <li><strong>Commits</strong> - Write clear, descriptive commit messages</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>What to Contribute</h2>

      <div class="contribution-types">
        <div class="contribution-card">
          <h3>üêõ Bug Fixes</h3>
          <p>Found a bug? Please create an issue first, then submit a PR with the fix.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="contribution-card">
          <h3>‚ú® Features</h3>
          <p>Have an idea for a new feature? Open an issue to discuss it before implementing.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="contribution-card">
          <h3>üìù Documentation</h3>
          <p>Improve docs, add examples, fix typos. Documentation PRs are always welcome!</p>
        </div>

        <div class="contribution-card">
          <h3>üß™ Tests</h3>
          <p>Add test coverage for untested code or improve existing tests.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Pull Request Process</h2>

      <ol>
        <li>Ensure all tests pass</li>
        <li>Update documentation as needed</li>
        <li>Follow the existing code style</li>
        <li>Write clear commit messages</li>
        <li>Reference any related issues in your PR description</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Code of Conduct</h2>

      <p>
        Be respectful and inclusive. We want this project to be welcoming to contributors
        of all skill levels and backgrounds.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Questions?</h2>

      <p>
        If you have questions about contributing, feel free to:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>Open an issue on <a href="https://github.com/ivmarcos/react-to-pdf/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a></li>
        <li>Check the <a href="/react-to-pdf/faq">FAQ</a></li>
        <li>Review existing <a href="https://github.com/ivmarcos/react-to-pdf/pulls" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">pull requests</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <div class="thank-you">
      <h2>Thank You! üéâ</h2>
      <p>Your contributions make React to PDF better for everyone!</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .contributing-container {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 60px 20px;
  }

  .contributing-container h1 {
    font-size: 42px;
    color: #0f172a;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .intro {
    font-size: 20px;
    color: #64748b;
    margin-bottom: 60px;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 60px;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 28px;
    color: #0f172a;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    padding-bottom: 10px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #e2e8f0;
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 20px;
    color: #0f172a;
    margin-top: 30px;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
  }

  p {
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #475569;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
  }

  ul, ol {
    margin: 20px 0;
    padding-left: 30px;
  }

  li {
    margin: 10px 0;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #475569;
  }

  a {
    color: #0ea5e9;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .contribution-types {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 20px;
    margin: 30px 0;
  }

  .contribution-card {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 25px;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .contribution-card:hover {
    border-color: #0ea5e9;
  }

  .contribution-card h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    font-size: 18px;
  }

  .contribution-card p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 14px;
  }

  .thank-you {
    margin-top: 80px;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 40px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
    border-radius: 12px;
    color: white;
  }

  .thank-you h2 {
    margin: 0 0 15px 0;
    font-size: 32px;
    border: none;
    color: white;
  }

  .thank-you p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 18px;
    color: white;
  }
</style>
